INSERT INTO `hesk_tickets` VALUES (172, 'VW3NDJ1M4P', 'Emma Warwick', 'ejwarwick@googlemail.com', 6, '1', 'Pintail / Turnstone', 'There is an error somewhere in your accommodation system.  The property Pintail in central Bamburgh was showing up as available for w/b 16th Oct in your system.  My husband made a booking via your site, but the confirmation came back as a mixture of confirmation booking and conditions for Turnstone Cottage.  The owner of both properties called us from Italy, confused, and said Pintail was unavailable but instead we could have Turnstone that he described as ''on the same site''.  I took this to mean ''in the same location'' in central Bamburgh, but on reflection he must have meant ''on same website''.  As it was a ''phone line from Italy and so not wanting to keep him on the line, I said that sounded ok.  However, when I looked up Turnstone on the web afterwards, it transpired that this is in a rural location some miles from Bamburgh and so is not suitable for our needs.  We have tried to contact the owners to cancel, but as they are in Italy, they don''t seem to be receiving communications well.<br />\r\nPlease could you fix the error on your site, and try to ensure the owners have received notification of our cancellation.  <br />\r\nI have marked the priority as high simply because of the short timescale in which the booking was due to start.  However, I appreciate it is not a major flaw in the context of the website as a whole.<br />\r\nThanks in anticipation for your assistance.<br />\r\nMrs Emma Warwick.', '2010-10-10 11:59:16', '2010-10-11 12:28:16', '83.100.162.128', '3', '0', '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `hesk_tickets` VALUES (173, 'LSVLX5RAMB', 'Graham Duff', 'lynnholm@btinternet.com', 5, '1', 'booking cancellation', 'Dear Visit Northumberland/ support @ eviivo (Daina if you cannot deal with this please forward)<br />\r\nBooking Reference:  WEB-NTPH21A865B<br />\r\nI received notification of this booking yesterday, Saturday 9th October 2010.  It relates to a booking made and paid for by a Mr Warwick for the property Pintail for the 7 nights commencing 16th October 2010.  That property had previously been booked for those dates and that booking appeared on the Eviivo website and others. The booking could accordingly never be honoured.<br />\r\nAt almost the same time I received notification from Eviivo of a booking from the same person for the same dates for a different property - TURNSTONE COTTAGE. That booking could have been honoured<br />\r\nI therefore contacted the customer direct to clarify the situation and was informed that the booking was meant to be for PINTAIL. I explained that that was already booked and offered him TURNSTONE COTTAGE.  That offer  was declined and he is a thoroughly dissatisfied customer.<br />\r\nHe sent me an e mail in these terms:-<br />\r\n&quot;Don''t know whether you got this email? We wish to cancel any booking, and you might want to suggest to visitnorthumberland to sort themselves out!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTim. &quot;<br />\r\nI was unable to give the customer any explanation for the confusion which seems to have at least two aspects 1) the double booking 2) the misinformation emanating from Eviivo (which also referred to 6 adults rather than 2)<br />\r\nThe customer, unsurprisingly, wants his money back.  I would be grateful if you would arrange for the credit card transaction to be reversed immediately,  This has caused great inconvenience not just to the customer but to me since I am currently on holiday abroad and have been put to the expense of phone calls internet access etc in attempting to sort this out.<br />\r\nI would be grateful if I could be informed when the credit card transaction has been reversed and for an explanation please.<br />\r\nI attach a copy of what I received from Eviivo.<br />\r\nGraham Duff', '2010-10-10 13:25:43', '2010-10-11 09:16:57', '82.193.29.47', '3', '1', '0', '24#Eviivo_booking_form.docx,', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '');
